# Muni Documentation Project Structure

This is a Next.js 15 documentation template built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, and MDX.

## Key Directories

- `app/` - Next.js App Router with dynamic routes `[[...slug]]`
- `components/` - React components organized by type:
  - `ui/` - Base UI components (shadcn/ui style)
  - `navigation-components/` - Navigation-specific components
  - `muni-components/` - Custom Muni components
- `content/pages/` - MDX documentation content
- `mdx-components/` - MDX component overrides organized by category
- `lib/` - Utility functions, hooks, and plugins
- `styles/` - CSS files with theme system

## Configuration

- [muni.config.ts](mdc:muni.config.ts) - Main configuration with navigation and theme settings
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration with MDX support
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts

## Key Files

- [app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx](mdc:app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx) - Dynamic route handler for docs
- [mdx-components/index.tsx](mdc:mdx-components/index.tsx) - MDX component registry
- [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) - Utility functions including `cn` helper
